11. Separate Property  
Petitioner owns certain separate property that is not part of the community estate of the 
parties, and Petitioner requests the Court to confirm that separate property as Petitioner's separate 
property and estate.  
12. Request for Permanent Injunction  
Petitioner requests the Court, after trial on the merits, to grant the following permanent 
injunction:  
 a. Petitioner requests that her contact information and residence information remain 
confidential.  
13. Request for Cha nge of Name  
Petitioner requests a change of name to MORGAN MICHELLE WILSON.  
14. Attorney's Fees, Court Costs, Expenses, and Interest  
 It was necessary for Petitioner to secure the services of Cooper L. Carter, a licensed 
attorney, to prepare and prosecute this suit.  To effect an equitable division of the estate of the 
parties and as a part of the division, and for services rendered in connection with conservatorship 
and support of the children, judgment for reasonable and necessary attorney's fees, court c osts, 
and expenses through trial and appeal should be granted against Respondent and in favor of 
Petitioner for the use and benefit of Petitioner's attorney and be ordered paid directly to 
